:"verb","usage":"escape(2x), save(2x), heal(1x)"},"G1201":{"id":"G1201","lemma":"δεσμωτήριον","translit":"desmōtḗrion","derivation":"from a derivative of G1199 (δεσμόν) (equivalent to G1196 (δεσμέω));","strongs_def":"a place of bondage, i.e. a dungeon","kjv_def":"prison","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"prison(4x)"},"G1265":{"id":"G1265","lemma":"διαμένω","translit":"diaménō","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G3306 (μένω);","strongs_def":"to stay constantly (in being or relation)","kjv_def":"continue, remain","pos":"verb","usage":"continue(3x), remain(2x)"},"G1223":{"id":"G1223","lemma":"διά","translit":"diá","derivation":"a primary preposition denoting the channel of an act;","strongs_def":"through (in very wide applications, local, causal, or occasional)","kjv_def":"after, always, among, at, to avoid, because of (that), briefly, by, for (cause) … fore, from, in, by occasion of, of, by reason of, for sake, that, thereby, therefore, X though, through(-out), to, wherefore, with (-in)","pos":"preposition","usage":"by(241x), through(88x), with(16x), for(58x), because(52x)"},"G1266":{"id":"G1266","lemma":"διαμερίζω","translit":"diamerízō","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G3307 (μερίζω);","strongs_def":"to partition thoroughly (literally in distribution, figuratively in dissension)","kjv_def":"cloven, divide, part","pos":"verb","usage":"part(6x), divide(5x), cloven(1x)"},"G1239":{"id":"G1239","lemma":"διαδίδωμι","translit":"diadídōmi","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G1325 (δίδωμι);","strongs_def":"to give throughout a crowd, i.e. deal out; also to deliver over (as to a successor)","kjv_def":"(make) distribute(-ion), divide, give","pos":"verb","usage":"distribute(2x), divide(1x), give(1x)"},"G1241":{"id":"G1241","lemma":"διαζώννυμι","translit":"diazṓnnymi","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G2224 (ζώννυμι);","strongs_def":"to gird tightly","kjv_def":"gird","pos":"verb","usage":"gird(3x)"},"G1291":{"id":"G1291","lemma":"διαστέλλομαι","translit":"diastéllomai","derivation":"middle voice from G1223 (διά) and G4724 (στέλλω);","strongs_def":"to set (oneself) apart (figuratively, distinguish), i.e. (by implication) to enjoin","kjv_def":"charge, that which was (give) commanded(-ment)","pos":"verb","usage":"charge(6x)"},"G1288":{"id":"G1288","lemma":"διασπάω","translit":"diaspáō","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G4685 (σπάω);","strongs_def":"to draw apart, i.e. sever or dismember","kjv_def":"pluck asunder, pull in pieces","pos":"verb"},"G1290":{"id":"G1290","lemma":"διασπορά","translit":"diasporá","derivation":"from G1289 (διασπείρω);","strongs_def":"dispersion, i.e. (specially and concretely) the (converted) Israelite resident in Gentile countries","kjv_def":"(which are) scattered (abroad)","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"dispersed(1x), scattered(1x)"},"G1263":{"id":"G1263","lemma":"διαμαρτύρομαι","translit":"diamartýromai","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G3140 (μαρτυρέω);","strongs_def":"to attest or protest earnestly, or (by implication) hortatively","kjv_def":"charge, testify (unto), witness","pos":"verb","usage":"testify(11x), charge(3x), witness(1x)"},"G1280":{"id":"G1280","lemma":"διαπορέω","translit":"diaporéō","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G639 (ἀπορέω);","strongs_def":"to be thoroughly nonplussed","kjv_def":"(be in) doubt, be (much) perplexed","pos":"verb","usage":"doubt(2x)"},"G1284":{"id":"G1284","lemma":"διαῤῥήσσω","translit":"diarrhḗssō","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G4486 (ῥήγνυμι);","strongs_def":"to tear asunder","kjv_def":"break, rend","pos":"verb","usage":"rend(3x), break(2x)"},"G1214":{"id":"G1214","lemma":"Δημᾶς","translit":"Dēmâs","derivation":"probably for G1216 (Δημήτριος);","strongs_def":"Demas, a Christian","kjv_def":"Demas","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Demas(3x)"},"G1298":{"id":"G1298","lemma":"διαταράσσω","translit":"diatarássō","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G5015 (ταράσσω);","strongs_def":"to disturb wholly, i.e. agitate (with alarm)","kjv_def":"trouble","pos":"verb","usage":"troub